Go here to create the web hook [Create Slack Incoming webhook]( https://slack.com/apps/A0F7XDUAZ-incoming-webhooks)
copy the URL you create and paste in a file to use to connect to Slack

In Slack you can quickly create a gipy to put into a channel message you send just type: /giphy your word   amd the gif will pop up
in your message.
Here we will make a webook to do the same through the dev code:


Incoming Webhooks are a simple way to post messages from external sources into Slack.
They make use of normal HTTP requests with a JSON payload, which includes the message and a few other optional details.
TeamTest at https://teamtest-space.slack.com

https://hooks.slack.com/services/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



To create a link in your text, enclose the URL in <> angle brackets. For example: payload={"text": "<https://slack.com>"} will post a clickable link to https://slack.com. To display hyperlinked text instead of the actual URL, use the pipe character, as shown in this example:
payload={"text": "A very important thing has occurred! <https://alert-system.com/alerts/1234|Click here> for details!"}
This will be displayed in the channel as:
![Slack text image](https://a.slack-edge.com/66f9/img/integrations/incoming_webhook_example2.png)

